@page
@model IndexModel
@{
    ViewData["Title"] = "Home page";
}

<section id="hero">
    <div class="hero-container">
        <h1>Introducing</h1>
        <img src="~/img/QCNewLogo.png" alt="" class="img-fluid">
        <h1>The Cloud Integration Accelerator for Tomorrow</h1>
        <h1>Developed by</h1>
        <img src="../img/CRLogo.png" class="img-fluid" alt="" width="300" height="60">


        <div class="row no-gutters">

        </div>


    </div>
</section><!-- #hero -->
<main id="main">
    <!-- ======= About Section ========== -->
    <section id="about" class="about section-bg2">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-6">
                    <img src="../img/cloud.jpg" alt="" height="450" width="500">
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-6 pt-4 pt-lg-0">
                    <img src="~/img/QCNewLogo.png" alt="" class="img-fluid">
                    <h3><Strong>is Cluster Reply's Integration accelerator.</Strong></h3>
                    <p class="font-italic">
                        Business today is moving quickly to cloud to drive digital transformation.

                        At the core of that move is the need for a cloud based integration platform.
                        This is typically in the form of an iPaaS or eiPaaS. QuickConnect provides the means to both speed-up
                        the process of delivering this utilising a framework built upon more than two decades of experience.
                    </p>
                    <ul>
                        <li><i class="bx bx-check-double"></i> Delivers a fully featured framework to accelerate development</li>
                        <li><i class="bx bx-check-double"></i> Encompasses the principles of an iPaaS platfrom</li>
                        <li><i class="bx bx-check-double"></i> Built using Microsoft Azure services</li>
                        <li><i class="bx bx-check-double"></i> Fully hosted in Azure</li>
                    </ul>

                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section><!-- End About Section -->
    <!-- ======= Why Us Section ======= -->
    <section id="why-us" class="why-us section-bg">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-title">
                <h2>Overview</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch">
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="~/img/why-us-1.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                        <div class="card-icon">
                            <i class="bx bx-cog"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">What is QuickConnect?</a></h5>
                            <p class="card-text">QuickConnect is an integration framework utilising pre-packed integrations across a number of well defined endpoints coupled with common helper components.</p>
                            <p>Integration typically is a long-term exercise. Leveraging QuickConnect allows us to get the first integration up and running in less than two weeks.​</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch">
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="~/img/Ben2.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." height="233">
                        <div class="card-icon">
                            <i class="bx bx-cloud"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">The Benefits</a></h5>
                            <p class="card-text">QuickConnect offers many benefits:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Speeds up development time</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Improves maintainability</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Encapsulates 20 years experience</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Built using best practise.</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Uses perfected integration patterns</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Provides the basis for an iPaaS</li>

                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch">
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="~/img/Vision.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." width="350" height="233">
                        <div class="card-icon">
                            <i class="bx bx-globe"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">Our Vision</a></h5>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                At Cluster Reply we have over 20 years experience working in the integration space.
                                Having been involved with Azure since it's conception, it has been our Vision to use that experience to leverage
                                the power of Azure for integration in the cloud.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                That Vision has been fulfilled with QuickConnect. But our
                                Vision doesn't stop there as we continue to hone and refine the accelerator.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section><!-- End Why Us Section -->
    <!-- ======= Tech Section ======= -->
    <section id="tech" class="tech section-bg2">
        <div class="container">
            <div class="section-title">
                <h2>Technical</h2>
            </div>
            <div class="row">
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch">
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="~/img/Architecture.png" class="card-img-top" alt="...">
                        <div class="card-icon">
                            <i class="bx bx-network-chart"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">The Architecture</a></h5>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                The 20 years experience and the power of Azure shines through in our architecture.
                                Building on the excellent Azure Integration Services and adding Cluster Reply know how, we have been able to produce
                                a highly versitile and adaptable solution for delivering cloud integration.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Our architecture delivers s a number of options from classic ESB, Event driven messaging to microservice delivery. Each easily configurable before deployment.
                                The result is a stable base for the delivery of customer solutions.
                            </p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch">
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="~/img/cofe.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." width="350" height="280">
                        <div class="card-icon">
                            <i class="bx bx-calendar-edit"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">What it Encompasses</a></h5>
                            <p class="card-text">QuickConnect encompasses the following:</p>
                            <ul>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> State of the art iPaaS framework</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Administation white label portal</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Common helper functions</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Core Services</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Deployment scripts</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> User guides</li>
                                <li><i class="bx bx-chevron-right-circle"></i> Documentation</li>

                            </ul>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
                <div class="col-lg-4 col-md-6 d-flex align-items-stretch">
                    <div class="card">
                        <img src="~/img/ball.jpg" class="card-img-top" alt="..." width="350" height="280">
                        <div class="card-icon">
                            <i class="bx bx-landscape"></i>
                        </div>
                        <div class="card-body">
                            <h5 class="card-title"><a href="">The future</a></h5>
                            <p class="card-text">
                                Cluster Reply is continuing to improve QuickConnect day-on-day. Already we have a standard version, a higher education version and work is continuing on a dedicated health variant.
                            </p>
                            <p>
                                Looking even further into the future, we are planning to extend QuickConnect to embrass the Power Polatform as a vehicle for citzen led integration.
                            </p>
                            <p>And finally, working closely with Microsoft, we envisage an on-premises version replacing the need for BizTalk Server.</p>
                        </div>
                    </div>
                </div>
            </div>

        </div>
    </section><!-- End Why Us Section -->





</main><!-- End #main -->